1
00:00:10,250 --> 00:00:14,083
[TWENTY-FACES]
You don't look well, Hanasaki.

2
00:00:16,375 --> 00:00:17,708
[TWENTY-FACES]
Haven't seen you since we played

3
00:00:17,791 --> 00:00:19,708
on the waterfront.

4
00:00:19,791 --> 00:00:21,208
[KENSUKE gasps]

5
00:00:21,291 --> 00:00:24,916
[TWENTY-FACES] Did you
have a fight with Akechi?

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,083
[KENSUKE gasps]
Oh, god. Twenty-Faces!

7
00:00:30,166 --> 00:00:33,333
[grunts, screams]

8
00:00:34,791 --> 00:00:36,625
[TWENTY-FACES] It would be
a simple matter to make you

9
00:00:36,708 --> 00:00:40,916
do as I say, but that
wouldn't be nearly as fun.

10
00:00:42,916 --> 00:00:45,541
[TWENTY-FACES] So, instead,
we're going to play a game,

11
00:00:45,625 --> 00:00:47,166
you and I.

12
00:00:49,625 --> 00:00:54,583
♪

13
00:02:19,875 --> 00:02:21,583
I didn't think you'd
actually come.

14
00:02:21,666 --> 00:02:24,541
You've always stayed
clear of the place.

15
00:02:24,625 --> 00:02:27,041
I'm only here because
you asked for me.

16
00:02:27,125 --> 00:02:29,166
It's still unusual.

17
00:02:29,250 --> 00:02:32,625
By the way, I haven't seen
Kensuke in a couple of days.

18
00:02:32,708 --> 00:02:34,000
[INOUE grunts]

19
00:02:34,083 --> 00:02:35,750
[OHTOMO] I called, but he
never got back to me.

20
00:02:35,833 --> 00:02:38,416
Did something happen to him?

21
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:39,541
What do you want?

22
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:42,708
Fine, be that way,
Mr. Frowny-Pants.

23
00:02:42,791 --> 00:02:47,041
Yamane! Any day now!

24
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:50,125
[YAMANE]
Yeah, yeah, I'm here.

25
00:02:50,208 --> 00:02:52,166
This should be
everything you asked for.

26
00:02:52,250 --> 00:02:56,208
Wire, spare underwater oxygen
cylinders, a lifesaver set,

27
00:02:56,291 --> 00:02:59,750
and the improved adaptive
camouflage umbrella.

28
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:02,166
S'all yours. I hope they
help you out in the field.

29
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:04,750
[OHTOMO]
Hm... Ta-da!

30
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:06,666
The ribs are made
with carbon fiber.

31
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:08,000
Compared to the previous model,

32
00:03:08,083 --> 00:03:10,250
it's about 47
percent lighter.

33
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:11,500
[INOUE]
Huh.

34
00:03:11,583 --> 00:03:13,500
At least act impressed!

35
00:03:13,583 --> 00:03:14,958
If it were Kensuke,

36
00:03:15,041 --> 00:03:16,666
he'd be bouncing off
the walls screaming,

37
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:19,166
"It's so light!
You're a genius, Ohtomo!"

38
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:20,666
I see.

39
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:23,041
He's just not that type of guy.
Don't take it personally.

40
00:03:23,125 --> 00:03:24,416
So is this everything?

41
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:27,500
[OHTOMO]
Hm. There is one more item.

42
00:03:27,583 --> 00:03:29,875
Huh?

43
00:03:29,958 --> 00:03:31,333
[YAMANE yelps]

44
00:03:31,416 --> 00:03:32,666
[OHTOMO]
Sleeping gas.

45
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:35,416
Just add water to
increase the potency.

46
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:36,375
[INOUE]
Not bad.

47
00:03:36,458 --> 00:03:37,625
[OHTOMO]
Not bad?

48
00:03:37,708 --> 00:03:38,333
[YOSHIO]
Hey.

49
00:03:38,416 --> 00:03:39,916
[OHTOMO, INOUE]
Huh?

50
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,333
You done yet?

51
00:03:45,208 --> 00:03:47,458
[KENSUKE groans]

52
00:03:49,708 --> 00:03:52,041
[TWENTY-FACES]
You were sleeping so peacefully.

53
00:03:57,833 --> 00:03:58,500
[KENSUKE grunts]

54
00:03:58,583 --> 00:03:59,375
[TWENTY-FACES]
Here.

55
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:04,125
[coughs]

56
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:07,208
[KENSUKE gasps]
What?!

57
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:12,166
[KENSUKE]
Where are we?

58
00:04:12,250 --> 00:04:14,250
[TWENTY-FACES]
And how is it? Tasty, yes?

59
00:04:14,333 --> 00:04:15,958
[KENSUKE]
Don't dodge the question!

60
00:04:16,041 --> 00:04:18,791
[KENSUKE groans]

61
00:04:19,625 --> 00:04:23,291
[TWENTY-FACES] I don't dislike
that look in your eyes.

62
00:04:23,375 --> 00:04:26,083
That said, I think
we can do better.

63
00:04:29,583 --> 00:04:33,041
[TWENTY-FACES] Let's see if we
can improve your expression.

64
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:34,916
Pay attention.

65
00:04:42,041 --> 00:04:43,416
[gasps]

66
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:47,625
[TWENTY-FACES]
Detective Nakamura

67
00:04:47,708 --> 00:04:50,625
is a skillful markswoman.

68
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:53,791
She subdued him without
hitting his vitals.

69
00:04:53,875 --> 00:04:55,250
[KENSUKE]
Brother.

70
00:04:57,541 --> 00:04:59,916
[TWENTY-FACES]
What is that? Relief?

71
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,333
[KENSUKE gasps]

72
00:05:01,416 --> 00:05:03,250
Even though he asked
to be killed out-right,

73
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,750
instead of having to
suffer through this life?

74
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:07,958
[KENSUKE gasps]

75
00:05:08,041 --> 00:05:09,916
[TWENTY-FACES] I doubt
he'll ever regain the shine

76
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:13,000
that you remember
from your youth.

77
00:05:13,083 --> 00:05:17,416
It's all your fault!
You made him this way!

78
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:20,416
[TWENTY-FACES] I extended my
hand when he needed help.

79
00:05:21,916 --> 00:05:24,000
[TWENTY-FACES] Do you
honestly think that's evil?

80
00:05:24,083 --> 00:05:27,000
[KENSUKE]
Damn right I do!

81
00:05:27,083 --> 00:05:28,750
More than Akechi?

82
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:30,291
[KENSUKE gasps]

83
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:32,083
Just... leave me alone!

84
00:05:32,166 --> 00:05:34,000
[TWENTY-FACES]
And what about you?

85
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:35,208
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

86
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:39,083
[TWENTY-FACES] Do you see
yourself as a valiant hero?

87
00:05:39,166 --> 00:05:41,375
A harbinger of justice?

88
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:42,958
[gasps]

89
00:05:43,041 --> 00:05:46,708
[bells chime]

90
00:05:46,791 --> 00:05:49,500
This unfortunate soul
didn't make it past ten.

91
00:05:49,583 --> 00:05:52,083
Her favorite things were
soccer and beadery.

92
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:55,916
And her precious smile
could brighten any room.

93
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,791
She needed new kidneys.

94
00:05:57,875 --> 00:05:59,041
[KENSUKE gasps]

95
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:00,041
[TWENTY-FACES]
And she would have gotten them,

96
00:06:00,125 --> 00:06:02,250
if you hadn't interfered.

97
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:03,875
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

98
00:06:03,958 --> 00:06:05,833
Remember the facility
full of NEETs?

99
00:06:05,916 --> 00:06:07,208
[bells chime]

100
00:06:07,291 --> 00:06:08,541
[gasps]

101
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:13,875
[TWENTY-FACES] Your actions
caused the death of no less than

102
00:06:13,958 --> 00:06:15,708
twenty-two children.

103
00:06:17,791 --> 00:06:20,666
[TWENTY-FACES] And that
number will continue to grow.

104
00:06:22,625 --> 00:06:28,125
But I... Those men... I kept
them from being butchered!

105
00:06:28,208 --> 00:06:30,500
[TWENTY-FACES]
Was that the right thing to do?

106
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:33,250
What of the children
you didn't save?

107
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:35,208
[KENSUKE gasps]
Shut up!

108
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:40,833
[TWENTY-FACES] So, are you
a good person or a bad one?

109
00:06:40,916 --> 00:06:44,250
[KENSUKE]
Stop it! I won't listen!

110
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:45,958
[TWENTY-FACES]
I understand.

111
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:49,083
You only perceive the things
that are comfortable.

112
00:06:49,166 --> 00:06:52,333
What a convenient way to live.

113
00:06:52,416 --> 00:06:55,166
Stop it!

114
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:00,750
[NAKAMURA]
Sorry.

115
00:07:00,833 --> 00:07:03,000
I won't have any work to
throw your way for a bit.

116
00:07:03,083 --> 00:07:06,500
[AKECHI] What? But I'll be
so lonely without my Nao.

117
00:07:06,583 --> 00:07:08,625
[NAKAMURA]
It's your own fault, moron.

118
00:07:08,708 --> 00:07:11,708
I shot a man because you
froze like a first year rookie.

119
00:07:11,791 --> 00:07:14,500
Sorry 'bout that. I owe you one.

120
00:07:14,583 --> 00:07:18,250
[NAKAMURA] Right, just "one".
Anyway, I'm sure a "Master

121
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:21,083
Detective" will have no problem
finding work without me.

122
00:07:21,166 --> 00:07:23,708
Hey, don't sound so heartbroken.
If it'll help,

123
00:07:23,791 --> 00:07:26,458
I can swing by and massage
those perky sweater balloons.

124
00:07:26,541 --> 00:07:28,250
[phone clicks]

125
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:29,125
[INOUE]
Ready?

126
00:07:29,208 --> 00:07:32,083
[AKECHI grunts]
Yeah, yeah.

127
00:07:32,166 --> 00:07:34,208
[AKECHI]
This place has seen better days.

128
00:07:35,625 --> 00:07:37,750
[FEMALE CLIENT A]
Please.

129
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:40,750
I'm counting on all of you.

130
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:43,541
Don't worry. This'll be
over before you know it.

131
00:07:51,125 --> 00:07:53,666
[TWENTY-FACES] I feel so
sorry for you, poor thing.

132
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:55,166
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

133
00:07:55,250 --> 00:07:58,375
[TWENTY-FACES] I know how
much it hurts not to be loved.

134
00:07:58,458 --> 00:08:00,708
[KENSUKE grunts]

135
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:02,458
[MALE HOST A]
Thank you all for joining us.

136
00:08:02,541 --> 00:08:06,708
We have a special
presentation in store.

137
00:08:06,791 --> 00:08:09,250
Our newest facility, Le Waqua,

138
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:11,958
is Hanasaki's tenth
large-scale complex.

139
00:08:12,041 --> 00:08:13,500
It's grand opening is
scheduled for tomorrow.

140
00:08:13,583 --> 00:08:14,833
[TWENTY-FACES]
A smile.

141
00:08:14,916 --> 00:08:17,875
You've never seen your
father do that, have you?

142
00:08:17,958 --> 00:08:19,291
[KENSUKE]
Shut up.

143
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:20,541
[MALE PRESS A] Could you
tell us what sets this complex

144
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,541
apart from the others?

145
00:08:22,625 --> 00:08:25,166
[I would have
to say, "Security".

146
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:26,875
[MALE PRESS B] Is that
because you plan to guard it

147
00:08:26,958 --> 00:08:29,166
with the latest model
security robots, sir?

148
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:30,916
[KENSUKE'S DAD]
Yes, that's correct.

149
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,083
[MALE PRESS B] An interesting
choice, considering the Hinomoto

150
00:08:33,166 --> 00:08:34,666
Heavy Industries incident.

151
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:38,041
Even the police are refraining
from using them. Why aren't you?

152
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:39,375
These robots are different,

153
00:08:39,458 --> 00:08:42,041
in both manufacturer
and capability.

154
00:08:42,125 --> 00:08:43,541
There can be no comparison.

155
00:08:43,625 --> 00:08:45,916
[TWENTY-FACES]
Well, now. Aren't you curious?

156
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,000
[KENSUKE gasps]

157
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:48,916
What do you think
he'll have to say

158
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,833
about the Hanasaki's
remaining heir?

159
00:08:52,916 --> 00:08:55,291
[INOUE] The building was
condemned 30 years ago.

160
00:08:55,375 --> 00:08:57,958
But, since then, anyone who's
been tasked with demolishing it

161
00:08:58,041 --> 00:08:59,791
has met with
unfortunate accidents.

162
00:08:59,875 --> 00:09:01,375
And, recently,
there have been reports

163
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:02,708
of spirits wandering the halls.

164
00:09:02,791 --> 00:09:04,958
So we're bustin' ghosts.
Sounds fun.

165
00:09:05,041 --> 00:09:06,458
Don't be ridiculous.

166
00:09:06,541 --> 00:09:09,458
All we're here to do is find
the cause of the accidents.

167
00:09:09,541 --> 00:09:11,791
Catch the spook, and the
case is in the bag, right?

168
00:09:11,875 --> 00:09:12,833
Simple enough.

169
00:09:12,916 --> 00:09:13,958
Ghosts don't exist.

170
00:09:14,041 --> 00:09:15,833
You might wanna rethink that.

171
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:18,500
After all, there's an
immortal with us.

172
00:09:18,583 --> 00:09:19,875
[YOSHIO]
Tsk.

173
00:09:19,958 --> 00:09:21,833
[INOUE] True, but that
doesn't prove the existance-

174
00:09:21,916 --> 00:09:23,125
[ALL gasp]

175
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:26,958
They must be angry. How scary!

176
00:09:27,041 --> 00:09:28,125
[INOUE gasps]

177
00:09:33,458 --> 00:09:34,708
[MALE HOST A]
Thank you.

178
00:09:34,791 --> 00:09:37,333
We'll take one more question
before wrapping up.

179
00:09:37,416 --> 00:09:40,291
The gentlemen in the
red necktie, please.

180
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:42,125
[MALE PRESS C] Do you have
enough confidence in the safety

181
00:09:42,208 --> 00:09:44,750
of the complex to
bring your family?

182
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:46,083
[MALE HOST A]
I'm sorry, sir.

183
00:09:46,166 --> 00:09:48,458
But questions of
that nature aren't--

184
00:09:48,541 --> 00:09:52,208
Of course, I am. I would
love to bring my son.

185
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:55,291
But he's so invested in
his curricular activities.

186
00:09:55,375 --> 00:09:56,625
I understand.

187
00:09:56,708 --> 00:09:58,708
No teen wants to hang with
dad on a business trip.

188
00:09:58,791 --> 00:09:59,791
[PRESS laughs]

189
00:09:59,875 --> 00:10:01,083
[KENSUKE grunts]

190
00:10:02,375 --> 00:10:05,666
[TWENTY-FACES] All adults
are liars, in the end.

191
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:09,458
I mean, it's not as if he
actually cares about you, right?

192
00:10:09,541 --> 00:10:12,708
You're wrong. I'm sure he--

193
00:10:12,791 --> 00:10:15,833
Poor boy. You're like
I was at your age.

194
00:10:15,916 --> 00:10:17,666
I know the pain you feel.

195
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,291
You know nothing.

196
00:10:19,375 --> 00:10:21,291
[TWENTY-FACES] You want
both your father and Akechi

197
00:10:21,375 --> 00:10:24,208
to notice you.
To approve of you.

198
00:10:24,291 --> 00:10:27,791
To praise you.
So badly, it's unbearable.

199
00:10:29,791 --> 00:10:32,958
[TWENTY-FACES] Still think I
don't understand your feelings?

200
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:36,791
[KENSUKE gasps]

201
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:40,375
[TWENTY-FACES]
I'll show you.

202
00:10:42,166 --> 00:10:43,958
[KENSUKE gasps]

203
00:10:44,041 --> 00:10:45,416
You see this?

204
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:48,666
This is what Akechi's
attention looks like.

205
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:50,958
[doorbell rings]

206
00:10:51,041 --> 00:10:54,166
Seriously?
You're being overprotective.

207
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,083
[AKECHI]
Mm?

208
00:11:03,875 --> 00:11:05,166
[YOSHIO]
Tsk.

209
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:07,833
If you heat meat to
over 150 degrees,

210
00:11:07,916 --> 00:11:10,333
that's when the
"Maillard reaction" occurs.

211
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:12,541
Causing the amino acids
and sugars to bond

212
00:11:12,625 --> 00:11:14,166
and bring out the flavor!

213
00:11:16,208 --> 00:11:18,125
In other words, it's chemisty!

214
00:11:18,208 --> 00:11:21,041
Cooking is just a
delicious form of science!

215
00:11:21,125 --> 00:11:23,375
Any jobs?

216
00:11:23,458 --> 00:11:26,125
Not today. I'm taking a
much needed vacay.

217
00:11:26,208 --> 00:11:28,916
Pippo and I have been
working ourselves coo-coo.

218
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:29,875
I see.

219
00:11:29,958 --> 00:11:31,208
[NORO]
Don't worry.

220
00:11:31,291 --> 00:11:33,250
I'm the healthiest member
of the club, by far.

221
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:35,416
I work out and
take enzymes daily!

222
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:36,708
Just look at me!

223
00:11:36,791 --> 00:11:39,458
B-T-Dubs, put in an app
before you come over.

224
00:11:39,541 --> 00:11:40,875
B-T-What?

225
00:11:40,958 --> 00:11:44,208
[NORO grunts] Forget about it.
The food made up for it.

226
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:45,208
All right.

227
00:11:45,291 --> 00:11:47,166
Uh! You're leaving?

228
00:11:47,250 --> 00:11:48,958
[KATSUTA]
Keep me updated, would you?

229
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:49,833
[NORO]
Huh?

230
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:52,500
I mean, I am a former member.

231
00:11:55,666 --> 00:11:56,750
[NORO]
Huh?

232
00:11:56,833 --> 00:12:00,833
His intuition's as sharp
as ever. Annoying.

233
00:12:08,166 --> 00:12:08,833
[sighs]

234
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:10,916
[AKECHI]
Hey! What's up?

235
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:11,916
[YOSHIO]
Huh?

236
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,041
[AKECHI]
D'you find the ghost yet?

237
00:12:13,125 --> 00:12:14,250
[INOUE]
Huh?

238
00:12:14,333 --> 00:12:15,375
[YOSHIO]
No.

239
00:12:15,458 --> 00:12:17,833
Okay. Let's try a
different approach.

240
00:12:17,916 --> 00:12:20,041
Like what?

241
00:12:20,125 --> 00:12:22,458
[AKECHI] It's probably best if
you handle this one alone.

242
00:12:22,541 --> 00:12:24,083
[YOSHIO]
You're skipping out?

243
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:25,583
That's what it looks like.

244
00:12:25,666 --> 00:12:29,000
I told you, If we're not around,
you can go nuts in there.

245
00:12:29,083 --> 00:12:32,333
It's a fairly simple concept.

246
00:12:32,416 --> 00:12:33,541
[YOSHIO]
Uh!

247
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:39,500
[TWENTY-FACES]
This gift. Is from Akechi.

248
00:12:39,583 --> 00:12:41,458
Does it bother you?

249
00:12:43,708 --> 00:12:45,083
[KENSUKE gasps]

250
00:12:49,166 --> 00:12:50,958
[TWENTY-FACES]
I was killed once.

251
00:12:51,041 --> 00:12:53,083
With this very gun, in fact.

252
00:12:53,166 --> 00:12:54,416
[KENSUKE gasps]

253
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:57,375
Of course, the death of
a single soul is trivial,

254
00:12:57,458 --> 00:13:00,583
as far as our friend
Akechi is concerned.

255
00:13:00,666 --> 00:13:01,708
[KENSUKE gasps]

256
00:13:01,791 --> 00:13:03,333
I mean, after all,

257
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:07,750
The "Master Detective"
has killed so many, already.

258
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:12,916
Heh. Listen to me.
Carrying on as if you know him.

259
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:18,500
[TWENTY-FACES] If you stay as
you are, he'll abandon you, too.

260
00:13:18,583 --> 00:13:20,000
[KENSUKE gasps]

261
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:22,166
[TWENTY-FACES]
He has an insatiable lust

262
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:24,500
for new thrills
and new pleasures.

263
00:13:24,583 --> 00:13:26,875
Constantly seeking the next toy

264
00:13:26,958 --> 00:13:29,666
that will be the source
of his amusement.

265
00:13:31,333 --> 00:13:33,666
[TWENTY-FACES]
Now that Kobayashi has shown up,

266
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:36,416
what use does he have for you?

267
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:40,666
He gives no thought to
toys he's grown bored of.

268
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:46,041
Akechi's only reason for living
is to chase the next big thrill.

269
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:50,791
But, to catch his desires,
sacrifices must be made.

270
00:13:50,875 --> 00:13:54,666
Pleasure can only exist
on top of detriment.

271
00:13:56,125 --> 00:13:58,416
[TWENTY-FACES] There is
nothing I won't sacrifice

272
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:04,000
to be his thrill. To be the
only thing he thinks about.

273
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:10,125
Tell me, boy. What pleasures
do you want to chase?

274
00:14:10,208 --> 00:14:13,208
What is it that you want to do?

275
00:14:13,291 --> 00:14:14,708
Well?

276
00:14:14,791 --> 00:14:16,083
[gasps]

277
00:14:21,875 --> 00:14:23,250
[AKECHI, INOUE]
Hm?

278
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:27,208
[WOMAN pants]

279
00:14:27,291 --> 00:14:28,500
[WOMAN grunts]

280
00:14:32,708 --> 00:14:36,250
[YOSHIO]
Hey! Stop running!

281
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:37,708
[BOTH gasp]

282
00:14:39,958 --> 00:14:41,416
[metallic thud]

283
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:42,500
The hell?

284
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:43,708
[WOMAN whimpers]

285
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:46,000
[AKECHI]
Looks like we caught our spook.

286
00:14:46,083 --> 00:14:47,666
[INOUE]
Please stop joking around.

287
00:14:47,750 --> 00:14:49,041
[AKECHI chuckles]
Yeah, yeah.

288
00:14:49,125 --> 00:14:50,833
[WOMAN gasps]

289
00:14:50,916 --> 00:14:53,333
[AKECHI]
Hey. You okay in there?

290
00:14:53,416 --> 00:14:55,000
[WOMAN gasps]

291
00:14:55,083 --> 00:14:59,000
[AKECHI] Hm. You have to
pay my fee, regardless.

292
00:14:59,083 --> 00:14:59,625
[gasps]

293
00:14:59,708 --> 00:15:01,250
Mom!

294
00:15:03,958 --> 00:15:07,416
Good grief. Did you really
think you'd fool us?

295
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:08,791
[FEMALE CLIENT A gasps]

296
00:15:08,875 --> 00:15:10,916
The lightbulbs in the
chandelier were custom LEDs

297
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,458
manufactured back in 2010.

298
00:15:13,541 --> 00:15:16,291
Furthermore, the building
in this photograph...

299
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:19,125
...Opened in 2020.
Aame as the Olympics.

300
00:15:19,208 --> 00:15:21,000
Neither the bulb nor
the building existed

301
00:15:21,083 --> 00:15:23,125
when this hotel was in business.

302
00:15:24,208 --> 00:15:26,291
[INOUE] I'm guessing you
planned to use our firm's recent

303
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:28,708
celebrity to make
your own headlines?

304
00:15:28,791 --> 00:15:30,708
[AKECHI] Would have been
easier than shelling out cash

305
00:15:30,791 --> 00:15:32,625
to tear the place down.

306
00:15:32,708 --> 00:15:35,625
It's a shame it wasn't a ghost.
Might have been worth something.

307
00:15:35,708 --> 00:15:37,166
No joke.

308
00:15:37,250 --> 00:15:39,750
But, even then, people would
have lost interest eventually.

309
00:15:39,833 --> 00:15:41,416
If you give something
enough attention,

310
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:45,333
you realize it's not a big deal.
It's how the truth works.

311
00:15:45,416 --> 00:15:46,583
[FEMALE CLIENT A]
Cold bastard.

312
00:15:46,666 --> 00:15:47,791
[AKECHI]
Hm?

313
00:15:47,875 --> 00:15:50,250
Don't you get it?
I'm desperate here!

314
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:52,041
How am I supposed to live?!

315
00:15:52,125 --> 00:15:53,125
[INOUE sighs]

316
00:15:53,208 --> 00:15:54,708
I'm a detective,
not a life counselor.

317
00:15:54,791 --> 00:15:56,041
Maybe you should find one.

318
00:15:56,125 --> 00:15:56,666
[explosion]

319
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,291
[ALL gasp]

320
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:08,333
[ALL gasp]

321
00:16:09,958 --> 00:16:11,416
[FEMALE CLIENT A]
How did it?

322
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:12,958
[AKECHI]
Welp. This case is solved.

323
00:16:13,041 --> 00:16:14,708
Let's get outta here.

324
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:16,708
[KENSUKE gasps]

325
00:16:16,791 --> 00:16:18,666
[TWENTY-FACES]
Why are you hesitating?

326
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:27,958
You refuse to say your desires
out loud. Are you scared?

327
00:16:28,041 --> 00:16:32,166
No. I'm not. I'm not!

328
00:16:36,916 --> 00:16:38,666
[INOUE]
What about Kobayashi?

329
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:40,541
[AKECHI] He'll come
out of there eventually.

330
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:41,958
Stop it!

331
00:16:42,041 --> 00:16:44,791
I think the kid might be
suited for this kind of work.

332
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:45,416
[INOUE gasps]

333
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:47,458
Kobayashi, I mean.

334
00:16:47,541 --> 00:16:49,666
He's a better detective
than most of you.

335
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:51,166
Even more than me?

336
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:52,416
[AKECHI]
Sure.

337
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,833
And Hanasaki?

338
00:16:54,916 --> 00:16:56,583
[AKECHI]
He's not a detective.

339
00:16:56,666 --> 00:16:58,541
[gasps]

340
00:16:58,625 --> 00:16:59,958
Akechi.

341
00:17:01,208 --> 00:17:03,375
[AKECHI]
He wasn't cut out for this.

342
00:17:03,458 --> 00:17:06,208
I'm done with his stupidity.

343
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:08,083
[INOUE]
You don't mean that.

344
00:17:08,166 --> 00:17:10,750
[AKECHI]
Enough. Just forget about him.

345
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:16,625
[KENSUKE grunts]
Stop it! Stop it! Stop!

346
00:17:16,708 --> 00:17:21,666
♪

347
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:27,833
[KENSUKE gasps]

348
00:17:30,833 --> 00:17:33,500
[TWENTY-FACES]
Do you still want to be his toy,

349
00:17:33,583 --> 00:17:36,333
even after he's
tossed you aside?

350
00:17:36,416 --> 00:17:37,875
[gasps]

351
00:17:37,958 --> 00:17:42,916
Unfortunately, The more you
cling to him like a lost lamb,

352
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,208
the more bored he'll become.

353
00:17:45,291 --> 00:17:48,208
You'll never bring him the
excitement he craves, now.

354
00:17:48,291 --> 00:17:52,250
[KENSUKE growls]
I'm not a damn toy!

355
00:17:52,333 --> 00:17:57,125
[TWENTY-FACES] True.
Now you're even less than that.

356
00:17:57,208 --> 00:18:01,875
As far as Akechi's concerned,
you're nothing. You don't exist.

357
00:18:01,958 --> 00:18:05,416
But, there's something
you can do about it.

358
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:07,791
Just make him into a toy.

359
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:11,958
[TWENTY-FACES] Imagine how
surprised he would be.

360
00:18:12,041 --> 00:18:17,250
Don't you want to make him pay?
To regret how he's treated you?

361
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:20,291
I can help you get
your vengeance, Kensuke.

362
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:23,208
[TWENTY-FACES]
I'll ask once more.

363
00:18:23,291 --> 00:18:25,500
[KENSUKE gasps]

364
00:18:25,583 --> 00:18:29,833
What... do you want
to do at this moment?

365
00:18:29,916 --> 00:18:32,041
[KENSUKE gasps]

366
00:18:33,291 --> 00:18:38,166
[TWENTY-FACES]
Is it to be... a pretend Akechi?

367
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:41,166
[KENSUKE growls]
Shut up!

368
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:43,500
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

369
00:18:43,583 --> 00:18:45,833
Dammit. I'm... I'm not!

370
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:50,500
[gunshots]

371
00:18:50,583 --> 00:18:52,041
[KENSUKE]
I'm not.

372
00:18:54,416 --> 00:18:57,041
I'm not anybody's toy!

373
00:18:59,916 --> 00:19:03,000
[gasps]
I'm not.

374
00:19:05,291 --> 00:19:06,875
[KENSUKE gasps]

375
00:19:11,625 --> 00:19:13,375
[KENSUKE]
I'm not like you.

376
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:17,958
I could never be!

377
00:19:22,916 --> 00:19:23,958
[AKECHI]
Let's go.

378
00:19:24,041 --> 00:19:25,708
[INOUE]
You didn't mean that, did you?

379
00:19:25,791 --> 00:19:26,708
[AKECHI]
Hm?

380
00:19:26,791 --> 00:19:28,458
[INOUE]
About Hanasaki.

381
00:19:28,541 --> 00:19:30,458
[AKECHI]\
Yeah, of course I did.

382
00:19:30,541 --> 00:19:31,708
[sighs]

383
00:19:31,791 --> 00:19:32,541
[AKECHI]
For now.

384
00:19:32,625 --> 00:19:34,083
[gasps]

385
00:19:34,166 --> 00:19:35,875
Whether he wants to
come back to us or not

386
00:19:35,958 --> 00:19:40,958
is completely up to him.
No point waiting for it, right?

387
00:19:45,125 --> 00:19:46,291
[sighs]

388
00:19:46,375 --> 00:19:48,875
[INOUE] So... Still trying
to kill yourself?

389
00:19:48,958 --> 00:19:51,125
[YOSHIO]
Of course I am.

390
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:53,500
Don't... you like
being a detective?

391
00:19:53,583 --> 00:19:55,000
Inoue.

392
00:19:55,083 --> 00:19:57,291
[YOSHIO]
It's not that.

393
00:19:57,375 --> 00:20:01,708
I... just have a feeling
that this won't last forever.

394
00:20:01,791 --> 00:20:03,125
That's all.

395
00:20:03,208 --> 00:20:05,916
Die before it's over, huh?

396
00:20:07,041 --> 00:20:12,083
♪

397
00:20:12,166 --> 00:20:16,375
[YOSHIO yawns]

398
00:20:16,458 --> 00:20:18,375
[INOUE]
This was here when I came in.

399
00:20:20,291 --> 00:20:24,583
[TWENTY-FACES] Hello, Akechi.
Lovely morning, isn't it?

400
00:20:24,666 --> 00:20:28,333
I've come up with a new
game I think you'll enjoy.

401
00:20:29,666 --> 00:20:31,291
[gasps]

402
00:20:33,166 --> 00:20:36,208
[TWENTY-FACES]
As I'm sure you've figured out,

403
00:20:36,291 --> 00:20:39,666
Kensuke Hanasaki is in my care.

404
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:43,750
A truly interesting
young man, isn't he?

405
00:20:45,708 --> 00:20:49,416
[TWENTY-FACES] Are you
going to come for him, or...

406
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:51,083
[screams]

407
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:52,666
[ALL gasp]

408
00:20:52,750 --> 00:20:54,250
[TWENTY-FACES]
Do you truly not care

409
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:57,333
if I keep your discarded
toy for myself?

410
00:20:57,416 --> 00:20:59,458
[TWENTY-FACES chuckles]

411
00:20:59,541 --> 00:21:01,041
Now what?

412
00:21:01,125 --> 00:21:05,458
[TWENTY-FACES] Try to find me.
Try to capture me, if you dare.

413
00:21:05,541 --> 00:21:08,541
[grunting]

414
00:21:08,625 --> 00:21:10,625
[TWENTY-FACES] Is this
entertaining enough for you,

415
00:21:10,708 --> 00:21:13,708
my dear Akechi?

416
00:21:13,791 --> 00:21:17,416
How I wish I could see
the look on your face.

417
00:21:22,208 --> 00:21:27,166
[KENSUKE pants]

418
00:21:29,875 --> 00:21:31,625
[TWENTY-FACES]
You're quite the actor.

419
00:21:34,166 --> 00:21:36,708
[TWENTY-FACES]
Now the real fun begins.

420
00:21:47,291 --> 00:21:52,250
♪

421
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:40,291
[TWENTY-FACES]
"Cruel Tool."

